M|model-selection|Works for product videos, cinematic videos, animated illustrations from reference images.
M|model-selection|| Model | Best for |
M|model-selection||---|---|
M|model-selection|| **Kling 3.0** | Most versatile; quality product/cinematic video from image |
M|model-selection|| **Veo 3.1** (Google) | High-quality cinematic video; good motion quality |
M|model-selection|| **Seedance 1.5 Pro** | Reliable, cost-effective; broad use cases |
M|model-selection|| Need | Model(s) |
M|model-selection||---|---|
M|model-selection|| Budget-friendly / high volume | Kling 2.6, Seedance 1.5 Pro, Grok Imagine Video |
M|model-selection|| Lipsync / talking characters | Kling 3.0, Veed Fabric, Hedra Character 3 |
M|model-selection|| Start frame + end frame control | Kling 2.5 Pro, Seedance Pro |
M|model-selection|| Long videos (>10 seconds), UGC | Sora 2, Veed Fabric 1.0 |
M|model-selection|| Animated illustrations | Kling 2.5, Seedance Pro, Hailuo 2.3, Grok Imagine |
M|model-selection|| Stop-scrolling / high-impact creative | Sora 2 |
M|model-selection|| Video editing (modify existing video) | Kling O3/O1 |
M|model-selection|| Motion graphics | âš ď¸Ź Not yet supported well by any model |
M|model-selection|> **Always prefer image-to-video over text-to-video.**
M|model-selection|> gen a still image first (gen Image node), then animate it (gen Video node).
M|model-selection|> You get significantly more control over the visual output.
